The '''Course de la Solidarité Olympique''' ({{lang-pl|Wyścig Solidarności i Olimpijczyków}}; {{lang-en|Race of Solidarity and Olympics}}) is a [[road bicycle racing]] stage race held annually in [[Poland]]. From 1991 until 1995, it was a race for amateurs, becoming a professional race in 1996. It was classified as a 2.3 event in 2003 and since 2005, it has been organised as a 2.1 event on the [[UCI Europe Tour]].
[[Image:23rd Race of Solidarity and Olympics (Poland, July 2012) - view from behind.jpg|left|thumb|250px|23rd edition, the last stage via [[Dynów]]]]

