{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Jaipal Singh Stadium | nickname = | native_name = जयपाल सिंह स्टेडियम | native_name_lang = Hindi | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Jaipal Singh Stadium | location = [[Ahirtoli]], [[Ranchi]], [[Jharkhand]] 834001 | coordinates = {{Coord|23|37|48|N|85|32|33|E|region:IN_type:landmark|display=it}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = 1977 | built = 1978 | opened = 1978 | renovated = 2013 | owner = [[Government of Jharkhand]] | operator = [[Ranchi Municipal Corporation]] | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 15,000 | record_attendance = | dimensions = | tenants = | website = | publictransit = }}
'''Jaipal Singh Stadium''' is a multi-purposed stadium loacated in the city of [[Ranchi]] in [[Jharkhand]]. The stadium was built in 1978 and was named after famous hockey player and captain [[Jaipal Singh|Jaipal Singh Munda]] after a request was made by [[Birsa Seva Dal]].<ref> [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ranchi/Jaipal-Singh-Stadium-to-get-international-look/articleshow/22242547.cms Jaipal Singh Stadium to get international look]</ref>
Since the stadium built, it was neglected for its sporting infrastructure but in 2013 [[Government of Jharkhand]] and [[Ranchi Municipal Corporation]] made plan to revamp the stadium into sports complex with aid from Central Government of India.<ref> [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ranchi/Jharkhands-Rs-650-crore-khelgaon-in-a-shambles/articleshow/20599150.cms Jharkhand's Rs 650-crore khelgaon in a shambles]</ref>
In 2008, a proposal came from urban development minister [[Raghubar Das]] to make a site of stadium into shopping complex but the planwas opposed by residents and sports lovers as well as Councillor. Sport lovers and residents also created '''Jaipal Singh Stadium Bachao Sangharsh Samit''' to save the stadium. <ref> [http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120713/jsp/jharkhand/story_15720341.jsp#.Vc8dw7Kqqko Revamp hope for Jaipal stadium]</ref>
In lasted proposal in 2013, the stadium will under-go changes and will have football ground, tennis court, badminton court, multi-gym, two pavilions, open air theatre, food court and shops. Gym will have all the modern equipment's as well as two pavilions for the players and football ground will be 300 meters long and 150 meters wide.<ref> [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/indiahome/indianews/article-2346932/Jharkhand-sports-complex-lies-unused-crumbling-despite-Rs-650-crore-price-tag.html Jharkhand sports complex lies 'unused and crumbling' despite Rs 650 crore price tag] </ref> <ref> [http://sports.ndtv.com/world-cup-2011/news/168852-national-games-begins-with-a-colourful-opening-ceremony National Games begins with a colourful opening ceremony]</ref>
