{{Infobox stadium | name = Roumdé Adjia Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = Roumdé Adjia Stadium.png | logo_caption = Roumdé Adjia Stadium (rendering) | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Garoua]], [[Cameroon]] | coordinates = {{Coord|9|19|34|N|13|23|57|E|type:landmark|display=it}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1978 | renovated = December 2018 (expected)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://actucameroun.com/2018/03/09/can-2019-stade-de-roumde-adjia-sera-pret-decembre-2018/|title=CAN 2019: Le stade de Roumde Adjia sera prêt en décembre 2018|date=9 March 2018|publisher=Actu Cameroun|language=fr}}</ref> | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = [[Mota-Engil]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeuneafrique.com/mag/557567/economie/construction-le-portugais-mota-engil-se-convertit-a-la-francophonie/|title=Construction : le portugais Mota Engil se convertit à la francophonie|date=16 May 2018|publisher=Jeune Afrique|language=fr}}</ref> | capacity = 30,000 | suites = | record_attendance = 18,000 | dimensions = 68×105m | acreage = | tenants = [[Cotonsport Garoua]] }} '''Stade Roumdé Adjia''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Garoua]], Cameroon. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. It serves as a home ground of [[Cotonsport Garoua]]. The stadium holds 30,000 people and was built in 1978. The capacity is 22,000 people. This stadium is set to be one of the stadiums used in the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations|African Cup of Nations in 2019]]. It's actually renovated by [[Mota-Engil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsducamer.com/inspection-caf-antony-baffoe-gronde-garoua-rassure-le-cameroun-avance/|title=Inspection Caf : Antony Baffoe gronde, Garoua rassure, le Cameroun avance|publisher=News du Camer|date=17 August 2018|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.camernews.com/infrastructures-sportives-bientot-cinq-stades-modernes-dans-le-nord/|title=Infrastructures sportives. Bientôt cinq stades modernes dans le Nord|date=27 April 2018|publisher=CamerNews|language=fr}}</ref>
