'''Tahir Jelani Walsh''' (born 24 February 1994) is an [[Antigua and Barbuda|Antiguan]] [[sprint (running)|sprinter]]. He finished fourth in the [[Athletics at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics&nbsp;– Boys' 100 metres|boys' 100 metres]] at the [[2010 Summer Youth Olympics]].<ref>http://www.antiguaobserver.com/?p=40715</ref> At the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], he competed as a member of the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|men's 4 × 100 m relay]] team. The team finished 6th in their heat with a season's best time of 38.44 seconds, but did not qualify for the final.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-mens-4-x-100m-relay |title=Rio 2016 |website=Rio 2016 |access-date=2016-09-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160902120902/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-mens-4-x-100m-relay |archivedate=2016-09-02 |df= }}</ref>

